{"questionId":"9371","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Adam sets out for a hike from his camp at point A. He hikes at an average speed of 4.2 km/h&nbsp;for 45 minutes, on a bearing of 035° from the camp, until he stops for a break at point B.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/29cd66593bc90b834b712953163ad368c89e6c1c.png\"></p>\n<p>Adam leaves point B on a bearing of 114° and continues to hike for a distance of 4.6‌ km until&nbsp;he reaches point C.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/796c322c088c456746e923fb6249590a8953f47c.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{A}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>C</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach to find angle BCA&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(<em><strong>M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em> sine rule</p>\n<p>correct substitution into sine rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp;&nbsp;</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{sin}}\\left( {{\\text{B}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{A}}} \\right)}}{{3.15}} = \\frac{{{\\text{sin}}\\,{\\text{101}}}}{{6.0507 \\ldots }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>B</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mover>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>C</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>∧</mo>\n          </mover>\n          <mo>⁡</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>A</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3.15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>101</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6.0507</mn>\n      <mo>…</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{A}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>C</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> = 30.7°&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9371","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.7c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find B C ∧ ⁡ A .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Applications: angles of elevation and depression, bearings"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}